column9: Centered around racialized minorities - but open for everyone
column13:
This event will center voices of queer ethnic minorities. Individuals who fall under this category are unfortunately too often discussed and spoken about - instead of being listened to - despite being a broad and diverse part of the community, locally as well as globally. 
Thus, a central part of this event will be a panel discussion on intersecting identities, challenges, and personal experiences both in and out of the LGBTQIA+ community, based on the lived experiences of our lovely participants. 
As a visitor, you will get the opportunity to forward questions to the panel through the app ‚ÄòMenti‚Äô. 

Guidelines:
- Refrain from recording or photographing during the panel discussion.
- Be mindful of the space that you are in, make room for others and if you need to leave during the talk, be as quiet as possible.
- Please be respectful of the participants and their right to privacy and personal space, both during and after the event.

In celebration of Aarhus Pride, we‚Äôre opening our doors and inviting you to a space where queer and other marginalized voices can be heard. Maybe you have a pride speech, a queer poem, a love song, a short performance, or something else you'd like to share? Take the stage üé§

Sabaah is a community for LGBTQIA+ people with an ethnic minority background, but for this event, we are opening our doors to everyone who wants to experience our space or take part in the open mic.
